                           DESCRiPTiON 
                          
In this game show, a group of contestants act as judges and examine video
footage of numerous homes, in which they have to use the items contained within
the home to guess which celebrity lives in the house. The creators ensure that
there is always enough evidence within the video footage to permit most people
to eventually determine the right celebrity, though it isnt guaranteed that the
judges will succeed.
 
 The series was originally broadcast on ITV1 in a prime time slot but moved to
Sky One in 1996. In 1997 the show moved networks again and was broadcast on BBC
One in a daytime slot. The shows has been hosted by Sir David Frost from the
very beginning. The most recent series have been broadcast on BBC TWO.
